=====Meteg=====
{{main|Meteg}}

By adding a vertical line (called ''[[Meteg]]'') underneath the letter and to the left of the vowel point, the vowel is made long. The ''meteg'' is only used in [[Biblical Hebrew]], not [[Modern Hebrew]].

=====Sh'va=====
{{main|Sh'va}}

By adding two vertical dots (called ''[[Sh'va]]'') underneath the letter, the vowel is made very short. When sh'va is placed on the first letter of the word, mostly it is "Ã¨" (but in some instances, it makes the first letter silent without a vowel (vowel-less): e.g. '''<big>×•Ö°</big>''' ''wÃ¨'' to "w")

