=== Letters that do not link to a following letter ===
Seven letters ({{lang|fa|Ùˆ}}, {{lang|fa|Ú˜}}, {{lang|fa|Ø²}}, {{lang|fa|Ø±}}, {{lang|fa|Ø°}}, {{lang|fa|Ø¯}}, {{lang|fa|Ø§}}) do not connect to a following letter, unlike the rest of the letters of the alphabet. The seven letters have the same form in isolated and initial position and a second form in medial and final position. For example, when the letter {{lang|fa|Ø§}} {{transl|fa|alef}} is at the beginning of a word such as {{lang|fa|Ø§ÛŒÙ†Ø¬Ø§}} {{transl|fa|injÃ¢}} ("here"), the same form is used as in an isolated {{transl|fa|alef}}. In the case of {{lang|fa|Ø§Ù…Ø±ÙˆØ²}} {{transl|fa|emruz}} ("today"), the letter {{lang|fa|Ø±}} {{transl|fa|re}} takes the final form and the letter {{lang|fa|Ùˆ}} {{transl|fa|vÃ¢v}} takes the isolated form, but they are in the middle of the word, and {{lang|fa|Ø²}} also has its isolated form, but it occurs at the end of the word.

===Diacritics===
Persian script has adopted a subset of [[Arabic diacritics]]: zebar {{IPAslink|Ã¦}} ({{transl|ar|ALA|fatá¸¥ah}} in Arabic), zir {{IPAslink|e}} ({{transl|ar|ALA|kasrah}} in Arabic), and piÅ¡ {{IPA|/}}{{IPAlink|o}}{{IPA link|uÌ¯}}{{IPA|/}} ''or'' {{IPAslink|o}} ({{transl|ar|ALA|á¸ammah}} in Arabic, pronounced ''zamme'' in [[Western Persian]]), [[Nunation|tanwÄ«ne nasb]] {{IPA|/Ã¦n/}} and [[Å¡addah]] ([[gemination]]). Other Arabic diacritics may be seen in Arabic loanwords.

